   and Vyhmeister, E. and Ostberg, P-O},
Title = {The ASSISTANT project: AI for high level decisions in manufacturing},
Journal = {INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF PRODUCTION RESEARCH},
Year = {2023},
Volume = {61},
Number = {7},
Pages = {2288-2306},
Month = {APR 3},
Abstract = {This paper outlines the main idea and approach of the H2020 ASSISTANT
   (LeArning and robuSt deciSIon SupporT systems for agile mANufacTuring
   environments) project. ASSISTANT is aimed at the investigation of
   AI-based tools for adaptive manufacturing environments, and focuses on
   the development of a set of digital twins for integration with,
   management of, and decision support for production planning and control.
   The ASSISTANT tools are based on the approach of extending generative
   design, an established methodology for product design, to a broader set
   of manufacturing decision making processes; and to make use of machine
   learning, optimisation, and simulation techniques to produce executable
   models capable of ethical reasoning and data-driven decision making for
   manufacturing systems. Combining human control and accountable AI, the
   ASSISTANT toolsets span a wide range of manufacturing processes and time
   scales, including process planning, production planning, scheduling, and
   real-time control. They are designed to be adaptable and applicable in a
   both general and specific manufacturing environments.},
